    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-03-02T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-03-02T10:00:00-05:00" n="193"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d193">
                <head>193. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in the Philippines</gloss>
                    to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d193fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 110.11–DU/3–255. Secret. Repeated to Phnom Penh and Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Manila</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-03-02T23:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1955—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 54. Following represents tentative
                    suggestions <persName corresp="#p_MADII1">MacArthur</persName>,
                        <persName>Robertson</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BRR1"
                    >Bowie</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MCR1">McClintock</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_YKT1">Young</persName> after Secretary’s talk with
                    Cambodians and French on training formula:</p>
                <p>Assuming French reject or procrastinate on formula, we can take following order
                    of steps during next 4 to 6 weeks while Paris is ratifying Paris agreements: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Sign immediately bilateral with Cambodia to proceed with logistics and
                            costing. (The French would not object to this.)</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Ask Defense to send, as soon as bilateral signed, General <persName
                                corresp="#p_LBGG1">Lodoen</persName> to Cambodia to survey material
                            requirements, and size, structure and composition of Cambodian forces in
                            light of what we think their mission should be. <persName
                                corresp="#p_LBGG1">Lodoen</persName> should also be asked to report
                            separately his views on adequacy of French training and security
                            conditions Cambodia including conditions Cambodian forces.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Defer the training issue until <persName corresp="#p_LBGG1"
                                >Lodoen</persName>’s report received and studied.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Then, probably in mid-April, put decision up to Cambodians to choose
                            alternatives already put up to them on training.</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>In meantime, make study of possible ways to set up a training
                            organization. Perhaps Colonel Rossin of <persName corresp="#p_ODLGJW1"
                                >O’Daniel</persName>’s staff and an expert on such matters could be
                            detailed on temporary duty to Phnom Penh to assist in this aspect of the
                            problem.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Request Department study above and comment to Secretary on his return Washington.
                    No action should be taken until then. If above approved <persName
                        corresp="#p_MCR1">McClintock</persName> can be instructed proceed with
                    bilateral.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
